    <!-- From the Titanium Server Admin Guide -->
    <p>A memory profile is a named assignment of huge pages for use as VM memory.</p>
    <p><image href="../../../media/CGH-2-inventory-details-memory.png" width="600"
        id="image_odj_4p4_ht"/></p>
    <p>
      <b>Note:</b> This feature applies only to servers in regionone.</p>
    <p>To view hardware profles:<ol id="ol_qcc_4l4_ht">
        <li>
          <xref href="../Dashboard/CGH-2-User-Dashboard-launch.dita#topic1160">Launch the HP Helion
            OpenStack Horizon Dashboard</xref>.</li>
        <li><xref href="../Dashboard/CGH-2-User-region-selector.dita#jow1432757989702">Select the
            appropriate region and project</xref>.</li>
        <li>Click the <b>Admin</b> dashboard, then the <b>System</b> panel, then the
            <b>Inventory</b> tab. </li>
        <li>Click the <b>Memory Profiles</b> tables.</li>
      </ol></p>
    <p>For more information on how to create memory profiles, see <xref
        href="../Inventory/CGH-2-User-host-management-detail-memory.dita#topic6841">Working with
        Memory Profiles.</xref>
    </p>
